	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">The Cradle Design</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442-1024x682.jpg" alt="cradleDSC07442" width="730" height="486" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-779" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/cradleDSC07442-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a>The cradle is designed to accommodate any book, up to the maximum size that the scanner can scan (12&#215;15&#8243;). </p>
<p>The cradle must meet the following criteria:</p>
<li>It must adjust to accommodate different spine thicknesses.</li>
<p> <a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1-1024x684.jpg" alt="CradleAdjust1" width="730" height="488" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-791" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust1-1200x802.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust-1024x684.jpg" alt="CradleAdjust" width="730" height="488" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-792" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/CradleAdjust-1200x802.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a></p>
<li>It must be removable to support the operator in the loading and unloading of books.
</li>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786-1024x684.jpg" alt="DSC01786" width="730" height="488" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-794" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01786-1200x802.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> <a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011-1024x683.jpg" alt="Removable_Cradle_DSC09701" width="730" height="487" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-299" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Removable_Cradle_DSC097011-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a></p>
<li>It must accommodate various improvisations and hacks to get unruly, damaged, and unique books to fit.
</li>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729-1024x684.jpg" alt="DSC01729" width="730" height="488" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-795" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC01729-1200x802.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a><br />
4. It must adjust in angle to press a book page flat against the glass of the imaging module. </p>
<p>Ideally, it will also support a few degrees of adjustment from the design angle of 100 degrees. In the case of this cradle, I designed some cam lifters that gave +/- 3 degrees of rotation by pivoting about the bicycle skewers, with the cam pressing against the cradle base. I&#8217;m still searching for a photograph of the protoype. The design files were lost in a syncing error with Dropbox.<br />
(cradle angle adjusting with cam mechanism pic goes here)</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->
